Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.94,0:39:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我并不责怪当时批评的人，我也不觉得批评我们疯狂的人自身是疯子\NI don't blame them I don't think anybody who tweeted Facebook is crazy was crazy themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.36,0:39:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们是对的，当时我们是有点疯狂\NI think they were they were kind of right we were a little crazy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.12,0:39:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[狗狗：你终于承认了]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.70,0:39:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,对于个人来说，演讲发布后某个时刻我觉得通过开源让我们更加融入社区的努力失败了\NI think there was a moment for me personally where I felt like you know my goal with the open sourcing of this was to get us closer to the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.02,0:39:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,并且我们反而退步了，我们可能对外界展示了我们根本不知道自己在做什么\Ncommunity and I may have set us back a step I may have demonstrated that we actually have no idea what we're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.72,0:39:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们做的事情和社区做的事情如此不同\Nbecause what we're doing is so much different than what the rest of the community was doing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.42,0:39:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,内部总结就是"好吧，我们搞砸了"，“失策了”\Nand internally there was a well we messed that up we made the wrong call
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.02,0:39:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我认为衡量成功的标志应该是"Wow，Facebook正在做一些非常酷的东西"\Num because I think the measure of success would have been wow Facebook engineering is doing some really cool stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.80,0:39:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,而不是"Facebook不知道自己在做什么"\Nand instead it was Facebook engineering has no idea what they're doing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.58,0:40:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,, 我记得从那以后，Jordan好几年都没再参加JS会议\NI think that gsconf um appearance might have been Jordan's last conference for a good few years I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.80,0:40:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom也一段时候没有再参加，React的发布演讲不知何故变成了黑粉们的盛宴\Nthink camokino didn't go back for a while as well it turned into a bit of a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.85,0:40:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,特别是对于React来说，它创新，有用，是提升开发者效率的一个礼物\Ntroll Fest for no good reason and particularly for something that was as an Innovative and useful and you know just fantastic for developer productivity and just it's literally a gift to everybody here here move faster
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.80,0:40:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,然而却遭到误解，承受恶名，特别是这些负面反应都是条件反射式的，未经过认真思考的\Nfor free to have people misunderstand it and say all these bad things about it that were just you know knee-jerk reactions without actually having taken time to think about it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.09,0:40:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom和Jordan对此感到挫败，特别是他们二人在过去的两年中也在Facebook内部遭遇过误解\Num can only must have felt very bad especially because both Jordan and Tamil had already gone through all this internally in Facebook for two years but
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.88,0:40:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,但是在Facebook你可以有充分表达解释的机会，然而对于整个世界来说第一印象更加重要\Ninside in Facebook it's a smaller scale you can just get in a meeting room and talk about it um but you can't really do that with the whole world can you
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.62,0:40:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,React的一些核心设计原则在Facebook内部是不言自明的\Nthere were some technical decisions that were made as hard to react that were self-evident
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.98,0:40:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但是对于Facebook之外的受众来说则显得非常疯狂\Nwithin Facebook but were like crazy when when um given to a different audience in the community
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.80,0:40:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,所以编程中有这样一种叫做"关注点分离"的思想\Nso there was this notion of separation of concerns
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.42,0:41:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,当时流行的做法是不同文件做分离，\N也就是你不应该把JS/CSS/HTML放在同一个文件里，而是应当每种类型内容一个文件\Nat the time like you didn't you shouldn't put your HTML CSS and JavaScript into the same file like should I really extract them out and you should like uh like have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.61,0:41:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,当时这种分离思想被认为是最佳实践\Nthis separation and so this was like very like the best practice at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.00,0:41:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,而React践行的"关注点分离"与此不同\Nwhat was interesting about the approach to separation concerns in react is that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.82,0:41:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在React中我们通过组件来做逻辑关注点的分离\Nyou separate your concerns into different components so rather than
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.68,0:41:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,对比来说，此前一个项目会按照视图和模型做关注点分离，\NReactsaying I have my view concerns over here and my model concerns over here
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.96,0:41:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,而现在React会按照功能来分离不同的关注点，\N比如这些组件对应新闻流功能，这些是相册相关的，那些是实现管理员面板的\Nyou say you have your news feed concerns over here your photo concerns over here your admin panel concerns over here
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.56,0:41:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是关注点分离的方式发生了变化\Nso it's a different way of separating concerns and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.83,0:41:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,React发布之后有很多人反对，一些人认为那些推出React的人都是小丑\Nso there was like a lot of backlash around like oh those people at Facebook are clowns like they don't know how to write software and everything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.80,0:41:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我们认为React在Facebook之外可能不会有发展前景\Nwe thought that react probably had no future outside of Facebook
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.42,0:41:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.80,0:41:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,对于主张开源React的人来说似乎所有的希望都落空了\Nit looked like all hope was lost for our friends at the Facebook office but
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.20,0:42:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,然而随着Facebook之外有人开始尝试React，转机出现了\Nfortunately someone outside of Facebook was willing to give it a chance
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.72,0:42:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,foreign
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.05,0:42:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.54,0:42:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,2013年我开始使用React的时候它在社区中还不流行\Nwhen I first started using react in 2013 it was not popular in the community it had just
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.52,0:42:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,当时React刚刚在一次JS会议上发布，我是在Hacker News上了解到的\Nbeen announced at jsconf I saw the announcement post on Hacker News
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.30,0:42:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我立即意识到它会对我当时做的一个项目有所帮助and immediately thought that it would be helpful for one of the projects that I was working on at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.83,0:42:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,那时我正在为可汗学院开发一个交互式的数学问题编辑器，项目的架构是面向组件的\NI was building an interactive math question editor at Khan Academy and it was something that had a very component oriented architecture
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.60,0:42:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时使用的是Backbone.js\NI was trying to use backbone.js at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.74,0:42:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是渐渐发现状态管理越来越难\Nand found that the state management was getting a little bit hard
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.82,0:42:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,当我审视React的时候，我发现它似乎解决了当时我所面临的问题\Nand when I looked at react I thought to myself wow this actually looks like it solves a lot of the problems that I have right now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.24,0:43:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我正在看的这篇贴文是我2013年写的，当时我才接触React，刚开始使用它一周左右\NI'm looking at this post from 2013 that I guess I wrote a week after I learned about react and it was right after I had
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.28,0:43:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,有人在Quora上提问: "如何评价Facebook的React框架?"\Nstarted trying to use it and somebody had asked how is Facebook's react
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.81,0:43:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然才用了几天，我还是决定根据自己的体验回答这个提问\NJavaScript library and I was a few days into using it and so I decided to write an answer to that question based on my experience
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.59,0:43:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我的回答非常正面，我记得我当时认为React真的解决了我的需求，\Nthe answer I wrote is very positive I think I was having a really good time using it and it was solving my needs really well
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.08,0:43:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一段是这么说的：\N"我刚刚使用React重写了一个两千行代码的项目，并向React提交了好几个PR"\NNone line from the post says I just rewrote a 2000 line project in react and have now made a handful of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.57,0:43:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"目前接触到的所有方面都感觉经过了深思熟虑，很骄傲能成为第一个非Facebook的React生产用户"\Npull requests to react everything about react I've seen so far seems really well thought out and I am proud to be the first non-facebook production user of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.00,0:44:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,接着我又谈到了一些技术细节，以及React是如何帮助我的，这个回答现在看起来就像是一颗时光胶囊\Nreact and I talked a little bit more about some of the technical details and how it was helping me it's cool to look back and it's almost a bit of a time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.68,0:44:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,它记录下了当时我激动的心情，尽管那时我才使用React一周时间，而这份激动持续了很长时间\Ncapsule to see how even one week into react being released I was already pretty excited about it and I think that excitement lasted for a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.30,0:44:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,接着我将当时手上所有的项目都用React重写了一遍\NI converted my entire code base that I was working on at the time over to react
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.20,0:44:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,结果是代码量减少，更容易理解，而且性能更好\NI think it ended up being less code and it was easier to understand and it was faster
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.78,0:44:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,很快我就决定继续使用React并将其部署到生产环境\Npretty quickly I said Okay I want to keep using react and I ended up deploying that to production
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.58,0:44:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我用React重写的项目应该是React在Facebook之外的第一次生产环境部署\Nmy my Rewritten code and that was I think the first production code using react outside of Facebook
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.56,0:44:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,foreign
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.07,0:44:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这时React做为刚刚开源的新项目，使用过的人还不多\Nit was a brand new project that had just been open sourced and not many people ad used it before
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.26,0:45:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,所以存在不少边缘使用场景，也就是此前没有用React实现过的需求\Nso there were a bunch of rough edges it seemed like you know maybe nobody had tried to use it in a particular way before
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.16,0:45:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,或者仅仅是文档没有很好覆盖到某些方面，而我又想超出设计意图去使用它\Nor if something just wasn't documented well enough and I was trying to use it a slightly different way than it was intended
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.48,0:45:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,自然地在某些地方React的表现和我的预期不符，我遇到一些bug和问题\NI ran into these little bugs or issues where it didn't work quite as I was expecting it to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.36,0:45:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,对于其中一部分问题，我阅读了React源码并尝试弄清楚原因，以便调整使用的方式\Nfor some of those I read through the source code and tried to figure out okay why isn't this working is there anything that I can be doing differently
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.02,0:45:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,对于其他一些问题，我最终找到了React核心团队成员聚集的网络聊天室寻求帮助\Nfor other cases I ended up joining the IRC chat Channel where a lot of the core team members were hanging out after it had been open sourced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.50,0:45:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他们不仅帮助我去使用React，\N而且随着我开始提isssue和帮助同个聊天室的其他初学者，\Nthat helped me get started not just using react but also starting to contribute to it as I started filing issues and helping other people who were in that chat room
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.34,0:45:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他们还鼓励我向React贡献代码，逐渐改善React\N as well as starting to make small code changes and starting to improve react over time
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.90,0:45:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophie自Facebook之外的可汗学院，她的外部视角非常宝贵，对项目很有帮助\Nher perspective from you know Khan Academy and just being outside of Facebook was so valuable  so helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.42,0:46:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophie一开始是外部的React使用者，然后变成了外部的React贡献者\Nso if he started as someone using react externally then sort of like moved on to being someone who contributed to react core externally
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.20,0:46:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,, 再然后成了React核心团队最重要的成员\Nthen became the most significant contributor to react core
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.30,0:46:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我们开始举行每周一次的团队成员会面并邀请Sophie参加\Nthen we would have these like weekly team meetings and invite Sophie to come
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.06,0:46:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophine也得到她公司的一个本地经理的批准，可以拿出每周五下午的时间来Facebook参加相关活动\Nand so Sophie like worked out with her local manager at her company to like carve out Friday afternoons to come to Facebook and hang out with us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.10,0:46:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,之前我们从开源社区雇佣员工然后他们却不再回馈社区，在我们停止这么做以后\Nand so determined not to do what we had done previously where we hired folks from the open source community and then they never contributed anything back
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.16,0:46:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophie反而成了有史以来第一个通过开源"招募"到的团队成员\Nshe became like the the first ever like open source recruited member of the team
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.16,0:46:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophie的参与拨开了React团队成员心头的阴霾\NSophie's involvement lifted the spirits of the react team
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.48,0:46:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,同时也让他们思考：也许，仅仅是也许，当时的JS生态不公平地排斥了React\Nit also got them thinking that maybe just maybe the rest of the ecosystem had just misreact unfairly
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.90,0:46:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他们相信人们还没有认识到React的价值\Nthey had something special they knew it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.34,0:47:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他们只是不知道要如何说服其他人\Nwhat they didn't know was how to convince everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.57,0:47:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得当时团队里的一些人，比如我，Jordan，还有Tom，Christadeau开始拥抱说服他人的挑战\NI think there are people on the team like me and Jordan and Tom and  who like the The Challenge and the the competitive nature of it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.90,0:47:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我们相信React是有价值的技术，我个人坚信这一点\Nwe knew that this was good technology and I was so sure of that that um
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.22,0:47:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为这是一个宣传问题，也就是我们需要改变我们宣传React的策略\Nyou know I viewed it as just a a messaging problem you know okay we gotta
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.58,0:47:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,人们现在还不能理解React的作用，我们需要帮助他们理解\Ncrack how we message this to people because they don't get it and we have to figure out how to how to bring them there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.12,0:47:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,开源感觉上是一个里程碑，是项目的终点\NThe open source feels like a milestone and it feels like this is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.52,0:47:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,但实际上这只是开始，因为一开始你的用户数量是零\NBut in practice it is just the beginning. Because\Nwhen you open source you actually have zero
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.76,0:47:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你要开始建设一个社区，修复所有的bug，确保它能满足人们的使用场景\Nusers, now you need to actually build a community,\Nget all of the bugs fixed, make sure it actually solves the use case for the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.16,0:47:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,真正的旅程由此开始\NAnd so this is like when the journey begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.80,0:47:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们准备大干一场，我们也意识到当你的项目如此特别的时候\NWe buckled down. And we also realized I think that really when you have a project like this that's um different
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.14,0:48:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要一对一地去争取支持者，这也成了我们接下来工作的重点\Nyou have to convince people one\Nby one. So I think that's really what we focused on.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.42,0:48:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们从中学到了很多，我们确信React框架的思想是先进的\NAnd we learned a lot doing that. We learned that the ideas in React are solid,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.04,0:48:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但是当人们考虑采用一个新框架的时候，首先遇到的不是框架思想\Nbut really the ideas are not what people encounter when they adopt a framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.18,0:48:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,他们首先遇到的是文档和错误提示，他们最最需要的是一种能够逐渐接纳这个框架的方式，而非一蹴而就\NWhat they encounter are the docs and the error messages. What\Nthey need more than anything else when they adopt something is an incremental way of doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.74,0:48:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,计策已定，团队成员们忙活了起来\NSo the team got to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.54,0:48:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他们开始专注于一次一人，一次一地，一次一个概念地传播React\NThey focused on spreading the knowledge of React one concept\Nat a time, one person at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.12,0:48:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,接着机会来了，另一个JS会议到了\NThen an opportunity arose: another conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.96,0:48:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,React开源当年的晚些时候，谢天谢地，Pete在JSConf EU做了另一次努力\NLater the same year, thank goodness,\NPete gave a talk at JSconf EU.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.56,0:48:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我的工位挨着产品基础团队，\NI had my desk over by the product\Ninfrastructure team. I was sitting next to Tomo
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.44,0:48:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我听到旁边的Tomo说我们资助了JSConf EU，\Nand he's like, oh we're just like sponsoring\Nthis JSconf EU conference
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.28,0:48:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们要在会上做一次演讲，好烦不想做\Nand we have to give a keynote and I don't want to give it. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.96,0:49:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得他是不想重温噩梦: 当你做了一次演讲之后本来准备放松一下，却被台下的观众针对\N I think he was like he didn't want to go through all that stuff. Because you know after you\Ngive the talk like people go and yell at you after you get off stage and when you go to\Nthe happy hour and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.20,0:49:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这种经历并不好受\NIt's not the most pleasant thing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.64,0:49:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我表示：我来！免费去柏林的机票给我，我去在会上做演讲\NAnd I was like, I'll do it! I'll take the free trip to Berlin and go give a talk at a conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.86,0:49:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"嘿！我是Pete，我今天要谈的是一个我们叫做React的框架，我们用它构建用户界面"\NHey I'm Pete, I'm gonna talk to you about a library for creating user interfaces that we call React.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.02,0:49:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,几个月前我们在JSConf US会议上开源了这个库\NWe open sourced this at JSconf US a couple months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.78,0:49:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在推特上我们收获了一些嘲讽和恶搞\NAnd we got some kind of sarcastic responses on Twitter, a little bit of snickering, that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.68,0:49:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,原因在于我们没有很好解释React的设计哲学\NWe weren't really communicating what we were doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.93,0:49:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"今天我想和大家介绍一下我们为什么这样设计React，以及React和其他框架的不同之处"\NI'd like to talk to you today about the design decisions around React, what we're doing differently than other Frameworks a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.96,0:49:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“以及怎样的实现让我们做出了这些设计决定，并且促进性能的提升”\Nnd kind of the implementation that lets us make these decisions and make them really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.96,0:49:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我的这次演讲就是要引起人们的兴趣："看，这就是React的不同之处"\NFor this talk it was like, here's what makes React different.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.07,0:49:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有说它好，我甚至没有说你应该使用它I'm not even trying to say it's good, I'm not even\Ntrying to say you should use it, I'm trying
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.83,0:49:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是尽力引起人们的兴趣，并展示React工作原理中一些值得关注的有趣地方\Nto say that this is interesting and there's\Na lot of interesting stuff about how this
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.02,0:50:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,这次演讲成功吸引了人们的注意力\Nthing works that you should pay attention\Nto. And that really resonated with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.31,0:50:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,这之后我们吸引到了一些早期创新者，用一个跨越天埑的场景来比喻的话，\NAnd so we got these kind of early innovators\Nyou know if you think of the crossing the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.35,0:50:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,首先吃螃蟹的是早期尝试者，然后是一些迟疑中慢慢跟随的\Nchasm diagram, where you've got your your\Nearly adopters and then you've got your laggards
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.15,0:50:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,再然后才是一些普通公司\Nand in the middle you have your kind of normal\Ncompanies.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.84,0:50:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这次演讲吸引到了一些React的早期使用者，他们开始在各自的公司布道That talk really got those early React adopters fired up and evangelizing React inside\Nof their own companies.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.46,0:50:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Pete的演讲过后，对React感兴趣的人开始增多，更多人想亲自验证下React中是否有值得关注的东西\NAfter Pete's talk, interest started to pick up. People started paying attention. They just wanted to, you know, let me just see if there's something there. 
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.68,0:50:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,React开始了慢热\NAnd so we got this kind of like slow burn of adoption of React.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.92,0:50:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,一些有趣的交流发生了\N And it prompted some really interesting conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.23,0:50:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,React引起了来自函数式编程世界的Brandom Bloom的注意\NIt recruited Brandon Bloom into the community\Nwho came from the functional programming world,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.23,0:50:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他开始跟他的朋友们说React值得关注\Nsomewhere. He started talking to his friends\Nand said, hey I think this React thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.18,0:50:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,然后Brandon又跟他的朋友David Nolen谈起了这件事\Nactually worth paying attention to. And then he goes and talks to his friend David Nolen
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.09,0:50:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,David是JS开发者中广为人知，受人尊敬的一位音乐人\Nwho is this very well known, very well respected,\Nreally great musician and JavaScript developer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.15,0:51:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得他当时在纽约时报工作，而我又正好路过纽约，所以见面喝了咖啡\NI think he was working at the New York Times\Nat the time and I was passing through New York to do something and we grabbed coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.30,0:51:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我的朋友Brandon跟我说我应该试试React，所以我和Pete见面后问了一些关于React的问题\NAnd I asked Pete some questions and Brandon  Bloom, that was my friend that said you should really look at React. 
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.46,0:51:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我了解React后感觉很激动，比普通的JS开发者要更为激动\NAnd the reason I was excited about it, more than I think you could\Nhave been if you were JavaScript developer,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.26,0:51:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,原因在于，JS支持多种编程范式，你可以使用OOP，也可以使用FP，JS开发者可以选择FP，但不是非此不可\NJavaScript is kind of multi-paradigm you can\Ndo object oriented you can do functional if you want but it's not required 
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.64,0:51:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,然而在Clojure/ClojureScript中FP是最地道的，但是还没有类似React这样的函数式编程UI框架，\Nbut in Clojure and ClojureScript functional is the most idiomatic thing and nothing existed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.72,0:51:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一直在尝试类似React的东西，但是我总感觉差点意思\NLike we were sort of like always trying to get things to work but it always felt like there was friction.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.32,0:51:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我当时还处于职业发展的早期，而David却已经是一个非常聪明的高级工程师\NI was still early in my career right and this is like really senior super smart engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.72,0:51:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,会面后的情景是他会问我一些关于React的事情，然后我会搜肠刮肚地尝试解答\Nand it was the type of thing where he would ask me questions about it  and I would stumble\Nto explain it and I would explain it poorly
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.12,0:52:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,然后他会用一种非常优雅流畅的方式确认他的理解，我会说"理解正确! 以后我就这样跟别人解释了！"\Nand then he would repeat it back to me in like a super eloquent great way and I was like yes, I'm gonna steal that! 
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.10,0:52:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,和Pete，Brandon谈过之后，我大受启发和震撼，我当时想"终于出现了这样的工具！"\NAnd so when I sat with Brandon and Pete it was like this huge light bulb went off, 
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.08,0:52:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“这太出人意料了，Facebook竟推出了这样一个函数式UI框架！我找到了！”\NI was like: finally this is so random, Facebook made this functional UI framework. Eureka! 
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.40,0:52:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,这绝对是一个"我找到了!"的时刻，React允许ClojureScript开发者终于能以函数式来写性能良好的UI了\NI mean it was definitely a eureka moment. It it did allow ClojureScript programmers to finally write a reasonably performant functional UIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.40,0:52:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,而且写起来非常自然，React和ClojureScript是天作之合\N And it was very natural, it was a very, very good fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.46,0:52:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,之后大概一两周，David写了一篇博文，叫做《JavaScript中MVC模式的未来》\NLike a week or two later he wrote this blog post
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.56,0:52:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这篇文章改变了React项目的发展轨迹\Ncalled the Future of JavaScript MVCs that\Njust like changed the trajectory of the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.03,0:52:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,从很多角度来看，你都会不能理解为什么React可以做到良好的性能\NIn many ways you look at React and you're\Nlike there's no way this could be fast, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.84,0:52:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,能做到高效，然而我在文章中展示了React和Backbone的性能对比图，React要好很多\Nno way it could be efficient. And then I showed these diagrams of what Backbone and React look like and React is much better. 
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.60,0:52:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,特别是使用可持久化数据结构的时候\NEspecially when you're using persistent data structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.11,0:52:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我的这篇文章纯粹是关于React设计上的技术优势\NSo my article I think was focusing purely\Non the technical benefits of the design. It
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.57,0:53:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,移除了人们心中对于React浅薄的迟疑，他们开始觉得“好吧，我也试试”\Nremoved the superficial consideration and I think people started saying, okay I will
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.10,0:53:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,不是“我会开始使用React”，但是消除了人们对React的偏见\Ntry it. Not I'm going to use it but it removed\Nthat "I'm never going to use that" to "oh
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.10,0:53:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,人们起了兴趣，开始愿意尝试React\NI'll give it a shot, this is interesting".\NOnce that post came out like within three
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.40,0:53:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,David的文章发表3个月后，React已经是人们选择JS框架时的有力竞争者了\Nmonths after that I would say that we were\None of the big contenders if you were picking a JavaScript framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.38,0:53:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想传播一种思想，你需要的是先说服一小拨人\NIf you want to spread an idea you need to really convince a few
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.90,0:53:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,然后让他们替你宣传，而不是自己在那吆喝\Npeople and have those people share your message,\Nyou can't just be shouting it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.73,0:53:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,更多人意识到React背后的优秀思想以及它可以让UI开发在很多方面变得更简单\NMore people started to realize that React had some good ideas and made UI development simpler in a lot of ways. 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.58,0:53:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,之后的一到两年间\NOver the course of the next I would say like year or two,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.50,0:53:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们会关注谷歌搜索热词之类的指标，看React被提及了多少次\Nwe're kind of just tracking things like Google Alerts of how many times is it being mentioned, 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.07,0:53:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,有谁写了关于React的推文，React衍生出了哪些项目\Nwho's writing about it, what projects are cropping up. 
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.18,0:54:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在构建前端web应用方面， Raact对于你需要的很多其他工具都没有定死\NBecause React was very unopinionated about a lot of stuff that you need in order to build a front-end web application 
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.78,0:54:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,自然地人们开始填补相关的空白，比如一批状态管理库开始出现\Nand you know people would fill in the blanks. And there was a bunch of state management libraries that cropped up 
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.20,0:54:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,还有一些路由库和服务端渲染策略开始出现\Nand there was a bunch of router libraries that cropped up and server-side rendering strategies. 
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.40,0:54:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是这一两年间React的采用比例慢慢上升\NAnd so there was this sort of slow burn of adoption over the next year or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.83,0:54:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,React是一个小型UI库，但是却可解决一些Facebook面临的最困难的问题，其他大公司也注意到这点\NReact is a small focused UI library but it proved capable when tackling Facebook's hardest problems and other big companies noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.14,0:54:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,其中Netflix当时特别需要重新思考前端最佳实践\NBut there was one company especially eager to rethink best practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.54,0:54:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.88,0:54:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,2014年我们第一次听说React，当时Netflix网站还是用Java Web技术构建的\NWe first heard about React back in 2014. The Netflix website had been built using Java Web.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.72,0:54:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,网站很慢，构建一次大概需要15分钟，因此我们决定迁移到一个更现代的框架\NIt was very slow, it took about 15 minutes to get up a build and we decided to move to a more modern framework. 
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.14,0:54:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,开关在这里\NThere we go. 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.04,0:55:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我们还不确定这个叫React的东西是否有效\NNow at the time we weren't quite sure if you know this React thing was going to work out. 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.66,0:55:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它刚刚出现，我们还报有疑虑\NIt was kind of new and so we were very apprehensive,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.24,0:55:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,特别是我们正在选择Nextflix网站未来10年的技术路线\Nespecially since we were building the future of the next 10 years of the website, right,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.53,0:55:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们选错了，以后我们可能要花数年的时间来弥补这个错误的决定，所以我们不想采用过于前沿的东西\Nwe make a bad choice now we got to backtrack years worth of work. And so we were very careful about not jumping into something that was too bleeding edge. 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.36,0:55:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的策略是让安排两个团队分别构建新网站的原型，两队都有30天的时间\NAnd so what they did was they actually pitted two teams against each\Nother. Each was given 30 days to build a prototype
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.86,0:55:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,一队使用Backbone，一队使用React，30天后React队伍的产出优势明显\Nwith one being React and the other one being Backbone and after 30 days the choice was clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.81,0:55:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“感谢各位今晚的到来，过去一年我们使用React构建新UI，很高兴能在这里分享我们在此过程中学到的东西”\NSo thank you all for coming out tonight. We're really excited to have you here and share the learnings that we've had, building the new UI in React for the past year. 
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.80,0:55:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,2015年我做演讲的会场其实用的不是这个，而是隔壁那个\NIt was not this stage, it was our next stage over, where I gave my React presentation back I guess in 2015.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.78,0:55:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但是感觉是一样的，我当时想"天！我要说服这么多人React很棒"\NSame feeling like oh my goodness I've got to convince all these people that React is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.89,0:55:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,还好我认为说服成功了\NBut I guess it worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.62,0:56:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我是使用React构建网站原型队伍的一员\NSo I was part of the team that built the new site using React.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.39,0:56:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始使用React感觉很不方便，比如写组件的时候容易放太多逻辑到一个单一组件中，逻辑上没有拆分\NAt first it was very clunky, like you're writing components and they're not quite, you know, you're putting too much logic into them or you're thinking too big. 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.45,0:56:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,其编程范式中并没有规定要如何拆分，但是随着你逐渐使用，自然地你开始从更原子化的角度思考\NIt's not clear the difference in the paradigm. And then you start to use it and you go okay wait wait wait I'm thinking much more atomic.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.74,0:56:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,正如React logo揭示的那样(一个原子示意图)\NHence the symbol of react. N(其实原子并不是React logo展示的那样，哈哈)
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.48,0:56:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你开始能够看到组件的可复用性，可测试性等等好处\NI'm thinking about this individual reusability, okay now I'm thinking about the testability of these components, I'm seeing the benefits now come out of it. 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.88,0:56:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以这里复用一下，那里测试一下，这里调整一下，那里加个prop\NI can reuse this over here, we can test this over here, we can change this here, we can add props in here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.08,0:56:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,然后你会非常激动地发现一种新的编程范式出现了，然后意识到它是具有革命性的，它会改变世界\NAnd it becomes very exciting to see that new paradigm come to play and go: this\Nis going to be revolutionary, this is going to change the world. 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.92,0:56:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们回到一年前，你们可能还记得当时的Netflix网站\NLet's go back in time one year to the old Netflix UI, you guys might
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.18,0:56:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,网站的整体感觉像是一种老旧的DVD包装盒封面\Nremember this one. The overall look and feel is kind of like this old DVD kind of box art
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.69,0:56:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,我想展示一下早期我们构思的新网站原型中的一个，它代表了我们认为新网站应该长什么样\Nfeel and so I actually want to show you one of the early prototypes of what we thought the new UI would look like. 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.42,0:56:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们意识到往后的世界会越变越快，web也是如此，一切都在加速\NWe knew that going forward the world was changing, web was changing, things were moving faster, 
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.78,0:57:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的竞争对手也在加速，所以选择React这个更加现代的框架让我们在构建网站的时候能够更快，\Nand our competition was moving faster as well. So choosing React and going with a more modern framework really helped us accelerate how fast we could build
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.26,0:57:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们更快地让变化成型，更快地让用户感受到改进，从而打造世界上最好的网站体验\Nthe website, how fast we could get new changes out the door, how fast we could try improvements for our customers to make the best possible experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.61,0:57:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我们能够走在web开发中UI设计的前沿\NAnd because of that we've been at the forefront of leading what UI design looks like in terms of web development. 
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.60,0:57:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,有很多公司复制我们的设计，我们视为对我们的认可\NWe've had a lot of companies copy us, which we take is a great compliment,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.72,0:57:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,而我们能成为先行者是因为采用了React，并受益于它能够支持UI设计上快速迭代\Nbut we were there first because of react and its ability to move so quickly in terms of design. 
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.66,0:57:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"这就是我们努力的最终成果，新的UI具有沉浸式的体验，完全使用React构建，我们对此感到非常骄傲"\NThis is how it ended up turning out and this is a UI that's big and immersive and completely built in React. So we're very very proud of it and the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.36,0:57:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.13,0:57:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Netflix现在开始公开地称赞React，而因为有了第二个大公司的背书\NNetflix was now praising React publicly and with a second big company betting big on React,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.80,0:57:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,React的受欢迎程度开始上升，事实上它开始具有了独立的影响力，React社区开始起飞\Nthe framework grew in popularity. In fact it kind of took on a life of its own and the community started to take off.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.99,0:58:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.16,0:58:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个时间点，React越来越流行，有人在Twtiter上提到: "如果能举办一次React会议不是很棒吗？"\NReact at this point was getting more popular and somebody on Twitter mentioned "hey it would be cool to have a React conference"
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.14,0:58:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,其他人也开始在推特上讨论这件事\Nand a lot of people started commenting and tweeting about this. 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.20,0:58:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我于是找到我的经理Tom \NAnd I went to my manager Tom Occhino. 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.42,0:58:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,他对我说，现在每天有50条关于React的推文，人们提到要组织React会议，我们应该举办React会议吗？\NAnd he was like: there's like  50 tweets about React today, like people are\Ntalking about organizing conferences, should we organize a conference? 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.26,0:58:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我表示举办会议是啥意思？我也不会呀，但是也许我们可以尝试下\NAnd I was like, I don't know what that means, I don't know how to do that, but like maybe. 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.90,0:58:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我是反对举办会议的，我认为React能取得当时的流行度而没有花费大量的营销资金是一件非常酷的事情\NI was very opposed to doing a conference. I thought it was very cool that we got so much traction without really pouring marketing money into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.07,0:58:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管React出生于Facebook这样的大公司，\NEven though React came from big tech company juggernaut Facebook, 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.32,0:58:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但是只有一小部分人非常希望它能够成功\N it was a small group of people that were like really dedicated to seeing this thing succeed, 
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.62,0:59:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,所以React有种小众独立项目的感觉，自带反叛气质\Nso it felt like this very indie you know Rebel Alliance type of project. 
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.02,0:59:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们不需要什么用户会议，我们有自来粉，酒香不怕巷子深\NAnd so I was like we don't need a user conference, like we got this cool vibe going on, let's see how far we can push it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.86,0:59:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,事实是我错得离谱\NI was totally wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.20,0:59:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们私下觉得举办一场React会议会很有趣\NWe had said to ourselves, I think it would be fun to host a React conference
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.63,0:59:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们不知道是否有足够多的React用户愿意参与\Nbut are there even enough people using React who would want to go to that, 
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.21,0:59:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,最终我们决定：让我们试试吧，先举办一次看看效果如何\Nand eventually we decided: Well let's try it, let's try to host the conference, and see how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.23,0:59:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,消息一出，一分钟内票就卖完了，处理支付的网站还因此宕机了\NWithin a minute, all of the tickets were sold out and we actually crashed the website that were handling the actual payment system.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.73,0:59:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Facebook的CTO找到我说有一些副总裁和其他公司的CTO希望能够入场，但搞不到票，希望我能帮个忙\NSchrep, the CTO of Facebook, actually reached out to me saying like: hey I have this very important like VP or CTO of some company that wants in that couldn't get in. Like hey can you do us a favor 
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.54,0:59:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我说我很希望能帮忙，但是票确实已经卖完了\Nand I was like I would love to, it's the CTO and everything, but like you know we're completely booked. 
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.22,1:00:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们非常惊讶票会那么快就卖空了\NCertainly we were very surprised about how quickly the tickets had sold out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.12,1:00:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没有意识到当时React生态的发展程度，以及早期React采用者创造出的狂热\NWe didn't realize just how much the React ecosystem had grown and just how much enthusiasm had been created by early adopters.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.61,1:00:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.69,1:00:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,会议举办的进度很快，我们就在Facebook园区的一个食堂搭建了会场，然后把人从最近的宾馆用巴士运过来\NWe put it together pretty quickly as far as conference planning goes and we just had it on campus in one of our cafes and we bussed people from the nearest hotel. 
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.18,1:00:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们没花太多心思，但是效果非常不错\NAnd it was very, very under produced but it worked out really, really well.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.12,1:00:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning everyone\Nand welcome to React.js conf!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.36,1:00:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The conference went like extremely, extremely\Nwell. As the organizer of the conference,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.92,1:00:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so excited to be here. And we open sourced\Na bunch of our projects like React Native
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.94,1:01:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and we started talking about GraphQL, about\NRelay. And so yeah it was a massive success.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.93,1:01:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There is this moment where you go and you\Nsee the stage and there's a giant wood cut
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.23,1:01:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,out like logo of the React atom. And I was\Nlike, my friend Maykel, the designer at Instagram,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.94,1:01:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,drew that in front of me like in the middle\Nof the night before we were going to open
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.75,1:01:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,source this thing, because we needed a logo,\Nand I was like: Maykel just like throw something
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.58,1:01:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,together real quick. And now it's this thing\Nthat somebody has built a giant sign with
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.73,1:01:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this on it and there's something about the\Nphysical impact of that, that's really cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.23,1:01:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the moment when it dawned on me that\NReact was becoming something different, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.49,1:01:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So for a long time what React was to\Nme was a software project and the reason why
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.35,1:01:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted people to adopt it was because I\Nreally thought it would make their software
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.81,1:01:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,better and make their lives better and make\Ntheir on-call rotations better. There are
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.15,1:01:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of reasons why I thought it would help\Nthem. After that conference what I realized
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.10,1:02:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is that React was becoming a community. There\Nwere meetups that would happen the immediate
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.61,1:02:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,next week that would have an expanded audience\Nthat they could go deeper into some of the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.88,1:02:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things that were discussed was really, really\Ncool and a huge recognition for us that the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.44,1:02:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,community was going to be an incredible part\Nof what would make React work and at that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.92,1:02:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,point was definitely already a really important\Npart of what had gotten React to that point so far.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.13,1:02:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.04,1:02:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's proven to me that engaging\Nwith your open source community is actually
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.64,1:02:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,more important than the technical work itself,\Nlike if you don't have a community you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.65,1:02:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,have an open source project. I'm excited that\Nwe just continue rethinking best practices.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.07,1:02:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank this community for making\Nit possible for us to keep investing in this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.79,1:02:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep working on it. That's all I got,\Nthanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.19,1:02:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a real high point for, not just for\Nme but for the team, and you know I think
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.72,1:02:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for Facebook engineering. I think we really\Nfelt like not just validated but like we were
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.68,1:03:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,actually like doing something that people\Ncared about and it was a really, really good
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.23,1:03:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling. It was already like more widely used\Nwithin the company but now it was like, okay
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.32,1:03:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how do we actually start converting everything\Nto React, how do we remove and deprecate all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.66,1:03:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the other frameworks and really like double\Ndown on React. Oh hey, how is it going? Going
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.56,1:03:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from like an interesting product to this is\Nthe next big thing. So it was a really amazing
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.44,1:03:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,time to be around and to get the whole company\Nworking together as one, you know, to make
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.59,1:03:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,this happen.
