Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.11,1:04:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other stuff.. So pretty good stuff, pretty\Ngood memories.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.32,1:04:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The team became inundated with questions from\Nthe community and a new developer enters React's
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.81,1:04:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,orbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.08,1:05:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.20,1:05:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do with my hands?\NSo you're saying that I should actually uh
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.05,1:05:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,start like uh.. Let me focus for a second.\NJust for the record, I did not create React,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.90,1:05:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,React was created by Jordan Walke.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.75,1:05:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I worked at a small startup. We were creating a sort
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.62,1:05:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of a digital publishing platform so there\Nwas a really complex post editor with different
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.94,1:05:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,blocks or like a scrollable text with like\Ndifferent effects and stuff. And so creating
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.93,1:05:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a dynamic kind of interactive editor for for\Nthese things was really difficult. And were
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.03,1:05:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,doing it with Backbone. I kind of wanted to\Ngive React a try because it was supposed to
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.70,1:05:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,solve this problem. The first React component\NI wrote was a like button so it was just like
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.18,1:06:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a button you click it and it says like you\Nlike this or you and somebody like this or
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.30,1:06:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you and like 40 others like this. So there\Nwas a bit of like a split and logic, and then
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.02,1:06:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the way you would express this in other Frameworks\Nat the time, you had to kind of manually watch
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.90,1:06:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what's changed and update it. And in React\Nyou could just say, if nobody liked this show
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.54,1:06:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this, if one person like this, show this,\Notherwise show this and like it's a very natural
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.35,1:06:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,way to write this kind of code. And yeah I\Njust wrote that button and I was like yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.63,1:06:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that looks good, ship it. And so we actually\Nrewrote the entire app in React over the course
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.98,1:06:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of like 9 months while still shipping new\Nfeatures. So React sped up our development
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.47,1:06:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so much that we were able to add new features\Nfaster, at the same time as we were replacing
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.27,1:06:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,old features, that's why I really kind of\Nfell in love with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.91,1:07:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of things didn't exist back then. Like\Nthere was no such thing as a React ecosystem.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.84,1:07:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you needed something, it didn't exist,\Nyou'd have to write it. So like you'd have
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.40,1:07:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to figure out how to do it because otherwise\Nyou're not going to have a product, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.26,1:07:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's kind of what I did for a bunch of\Nthings. One of those projects in particular
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.09,1:07:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was.. I just saw a big opportunity there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.07,1:07:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called React Hot Loader at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.56,1:07:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to give a talk about that, but\Nsomebody else had done a talk that mentioned
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.75,1:07:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it earlier at React conf. A really clever\Nfellow called Dan Abramov figured this out
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.76,1:07:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and he created the React Hot Loader. And I\Nfelt that well then that just wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.04,1:07:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting because people kind of already\Nsaw it which in retrospect I don't think it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.21,1:07:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,would be true but that's how I saw it at the\Ntime. So I wanted to kind of spice it up a
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.35,1:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit and I wanted to make a proof of\Nconcept of a thing I saw in a Bret Victor
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.96,1:08:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,demo that is often referred to as time traveling.\NIf you're designing something embedded in
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.20,1:08:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,time, you need to be able to control time,\Nyou need to be able to see across time, otherwise
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.63,1:08:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you're designing blind. I didn't really know\Nhow to do it but I thought that's a cool idea
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.39,1:08:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for a talk. So I'm gonna send the proposal\Nif the proposal is successful then I'll just
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.81,1:08:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,figure it out. And it turned out that the\Nproposal was more successful than I thought
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.54,1:08:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be and so I made a proof of concept\Nfor that and that proof of concept became
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.60,1:08:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,known as Redux.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.64,1:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So my talk is about developer\Ntools because React and Hot Loading and time
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.27,1:08:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,travel these are all developer tools. He was\Nliterally creating Redux in service of being
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.96,1:08:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,able to deliver this talk and I called it\Npresentation driven development because the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.85,1:08:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that shook out of it was you know this\Nsort of like canonical state management library
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.54,1:08:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for React apps for several years. Most of\Nmy work is around the React ecosystem because
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.75,1:08:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what inspired me to contribute to the\Nopen source in the first place, but there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.77,1:09:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are two particular projects that I'm going\Nto talk about today. It was very validating
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.12,1:09:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to give that talk but I was not surprised\Nby the response because well I had my doubts
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.85,1:09:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but also I thought the talk was good.. like\NI thought it's a really good talk. And I was
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.72,1:09:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,glad that people also liked it but I think\Nit was actually not the talk that was really
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.25,1:09:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like the moment for me. I think it was just\Nlike being there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.80,1:09:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It kind of felt like
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.35,1:09:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,going to Hogwarts for the first\Ntime. I think it kind of had this this feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.40,1:09:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because there were all these people who I\Nonly knew them as these avatars and when you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.39,1:09:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,meet somebody in person they kind of become\Nthree-dimensional of course. You kind of see
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.87,1:09:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole picture. And I think it was just\Nlike such a wholesome feeling. It's the feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.73,1:09:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are all trying to figure out what\Nwe can do with this thing and we don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.87,1:10:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it yet and we're just playing with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.92,1:10:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also where I met Jing Chen. I had asked\Nfor her advice before because she's one of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.85,1:10:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the co-creators of the Flux architecture.\NSo it was nice to meet her in person and she
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.40,1:10:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned that actually Facebook is hiring\Nin London. And so they arranged an interview
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.39,1:10:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for me right at the conference which was like\Nour normal interview process the same I think
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.42,1:10:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,like four interviews or something like this\Nbut I missed the second day of the conference
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.98,1:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but we just did an interview there and so\Nthat's kind of how I got into Facebook. We
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.10,1:10:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just quickly grabbed them out of the conference\Na little bit like on the down low and then
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.12,1:10:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,conducted the interviews in the basement of\Na hotel I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.69,1:10:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No Dan is special, he's always been a little\Nspecial.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.03,1:10:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess like I would think of myself
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.58,1:11:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as like maybe the first member of what would\Nbecome the React team as you know it today
