Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.58,1:12:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that on the team we were talking about internally\Nand so I just remember like, I gotta connect
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.15,1:12:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you with like Sebastian and Jordan and the\Nrest of the team. Yeah and then also I was
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.58,1:12:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like to the recruiters I was like yeah this\Nguy like we gotta hire this Andrew guy. And
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.81,1:12:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we were really fortunate early on\Nto have a bunch of people that kind of stepped
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.54,1:12:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,up and they were this seems cool, I just want\Nto be a part of this, I just want to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.06,1:12:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize it was kind of like a freshman\Nclass sort of feeling at the time. Sophie
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.46,1:12:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,had started managing the team around that\Ntime as well and I couldn't have really asked
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.28,1:12:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for a better both project and set of colleagues\Nand team to join. The beginning of phase two.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.73,1:12:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.54,1:12:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome! I feel\Nlike we really brought it home there at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.00,1:12:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Like man we're nailing this!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.17,1:12:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.49,1:13:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,React was now out of the hands of\Nits founders.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.60,1:13:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ready to take on new life in the care of a\Nnew community grown and future-minded team.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.25,1:13:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to watch some of the numbers like the number of GitHub stars
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.55,1:13:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or the number of npm downloads. On Google
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.66,1:13:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Trends, how many people are searching for\NReact and none of those numbers are perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.69,1:13:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but basically all of them kept going up over\Ntime and eventually got to a point where we
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.34,1:13:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at it and said oh yeah like millions\Nof people essentially are using React.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.81,1:13:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of little details in how we did\Nthings that encourages an ecosystem to participate,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.09,1:13:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that were critical parts in making it what\Nit is today. We didn't put everything in the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.06,1:13:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,framework. We left a lot of it to the ecosystem\Nto innovate. And we got a lot of contributions,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.38,1:14:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we got a lot of interest that way, we got\Na lot of things spurring from that. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.23,1:14:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,not ever a foregone conclusion. Like it's\Nstill surreal to me that it's as popular as
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.67,1:14:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it is. It's this great example of this like\Nunderdog technology within a big company where
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.55,1:14:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there could have been these forces that really\Npushed back on it. I think a lot of elements
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.04,1:14:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of good timing, good fortune, good luck, good\Nleadership support, all sort of like aggregated
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.31,1:14:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow React to be a success, that had we\Nmissed a few of those or had a handful more
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.74,1:14:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,things failed instead of succeeded, then I\Ndo not think React would be in the spot that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it is today. I feel like you can't take anyone\Nout of it and have it be what it became. I
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.84,1:14:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,think in the early days obviously Jordan,\Nright. Like this thing wouldn't exist. And
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.55,1:14:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jing Chen just absolutely critical. I\Nmean she was so instrumental in the early
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.56,1:14:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,days of React that it just wouldn't have been\Na thing that we cared about if it didn't prove
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.07,1:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,itself. And then Shane O'Sullivan is responsible\Nfor you know really I mean a very hard decision
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.44,1:15:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to like I'm gonna go this path instead of\Nthat thing. And then the engineers that worked
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.77,1:15:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on refining and iterating on it and turning\Nit into something good it was Chedeau and
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.00,1:15:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul O'Shannessy and Pete Hunt. And my manager\NAdam Wolff, when I was like you know asking
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.60,1:15:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,all these questions about like should we be\Ndoing, like is this even worth it, especially
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.86,1:15:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,after JS conf when we were feeling defeated,\Nyou know, he was there to pick me back up
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.78,1:15:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and be like: no look it is delivering value,\Nthis is good, keep going. And there's different
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.52,1:15:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,phases too right, you have the early, early\Ndays and you had the like for the next literally
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.15,1:15:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,almost we're going on 10 years now, with Sebastian's\Ntechnical leadership and Andrew and Dan and
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.30,1:15:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dominic and Flarney and Sophie and I just\Nfeel like it's just a group of incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.83,1:15:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,people and if you take any of them out of\Nit it just looks pretty different. It was
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.15,1:15:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,really a team effort, it was really a team\Neffort from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.28,1:16:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[Music]
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.07,1:16:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Misko Hevery says that awesome solutions\Nare rarely created by large organizations.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.67,1:16:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost always one person with passion\Nand vision that slowly start to infect others.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.28,1:16:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great summary of how React became\NReact. Because it was never inevitable, it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.37,1:16:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was always this wild idea that kept gathering\Nmomentum, person by person. And many expected
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.60,1:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,React to fail and if it weren't for the hard\Nwork of a few determined developers
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.88,1:16:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it very well could have.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.02,1:16:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the beginning of the React story.\NThe story of how a community transformed an
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.63,1:16:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,underdog UI library into the most popular\NJavaScript framework today.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.76,1:16:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is React Podcast, I'm Chantastic.
